Create AppImage

howto: https://forum.openframeworks.cc/t/creating-a-appimage-for-linux/33142

MyApp.AppDir/
MyApp.AppDir/AppRun    --- you donwnload this from [here](https://github.com/AppImage/AppImageKit/releases) get the one AppRun-x86_64 and just renamed to AppRun
MyApp.AppDir/myapp.desktop
MyApp.AppDir/myapp.png
MyApp.AppDir/usr/bin/myapp --- copy your OF app here  i copied  the bin folder complete
MyApp.AppDir/usr/lib/libfoo.so.0 -- copy here all libraries here (which displayed by the command # ldd MyDailyDesktopWallpaper)

make the MyApp.AppDir/myapp.desktop file like this

[Desktop Entry]
Name=MyApp
Exec=myapp
Icon=myapp
Type=Application
Categories=Utility;

----

download this tool:
https://github.com/AppImage/AppImageKit/releases/download/12/appimagetool-x86_64.AppImage

run it:

# ./appimagetool-x86_64.AppImage 'DailyDesktopWallpaperPlus.AppDir' DailyDesktopWallpaperPlus-x86_64-linux.AppImage

#END
